Server Rules

1. This community exists for thoughtful, good-faith conversation around [CREATOR / SHOW NAME].

Contribute to understanding.
Ask honest questions.
Disagree with ideas — not with people.

Low-effort outrage, trolling, and performative behavior will be removed.


2. Be constructive
Add context
Bring sources when making claims
Engage with what others actually said
Help move the conversation forward

If your goal is to “win” rather than to understand, this is not the right space.


3. No harassment or personal attacks

Critique analysis.
Challenge assumptions.
Debate conclusions.

Do not:
Target individuals
Use slurs
Dogpile
Intimidate other members

4. No spam or self-promotion

This is a discussion environment — not a growth channel.

Relevant resources are welcome.
Promotion without participation is not.

5. Stay on mission

Content should relate to:
The themes of the show
The episode under discussion
Directly relevant geopolitical developments

Off-topic posting may be removed to preserve signal.

6. Respect operational security and real-world safety

Do not post:
Sensitive personal information
Real-time location data
Anything that could put people at risk

7. Moderation is active and intentional

This space is curated to maintain:
Signal
Seriousness
Readability

Moderation decisions are made to protect the community, not to control viewpoints.

8. This is a community-funded public discussion space.

No ads.
No algorithms.
No engagement games.

If you are here, you are part of building a better conversation environment.
